To automatically generate a table of contents in a LaTeX document, you need to include a few commands in your document preamble and at the places where you want the table of contents to be inserted and where you want headings and subheadings to be created. Here's an example:

```latex
\documentclass{article}

% Add the command to update the table of contents
\usepackage{tocbibind} % if you want the table of contents to be listed in the table of contents itself

\begin{document}

% Generate the Table of Contents
\tableofcontents
\newpage

